She was a horribly teacher and rambled about nothing.  She is very boring and does not keep my interest.

Lecture was boring and unnecessary to attend. Exams are take home and written. She tells you what to know for quizzes and exams, so that makes them easier (and guides reading). Discussion is the only save for the class, so hope for a good TA.
Lectures were pointless.  She's very boring to listen to and reads slides verbatim.  She is most comparable to that old teacher in Donnie Darko.

Easy class.  Lecture is unnecessary to attend.  Professor Connell is very understanding.  If you miss a quiz she will most likely give a make up date for those who missed.  You can go to her if you have a problem.
Totally pointless to go to lecture. She reads directly off of her slides. She puts up lecture notes online, but they're hard to understand. The class can be very easy if you have a good TA.

Like someone else said, I too was scolded for asking a question.  She seems to not know how to communicate with students in lecture (focused on the content, not students as learners.
Very boring lecture. She gives you online notes for every lecture, but they are very disorganized and don't make much sense. Exams are take-home, easy class.
